<description>

The Account Transfers form contains From Office, From Client, From Account Type (Savings Account, Loan Account), From Account, To Office, To Client, To Account Type, To Account, Transfer Amount (required), Transfer Date (required), and Description. If the transfer amount exceeds the available balance, an error is shown. Clicking "Submit" processes the transfer, debiting the source and crediting the destination.

The Standing Instructions page displays a data table with columns for Name, From Client, From Account, To Client, To Account, Amount, Validity (From/Till dates), and Status (Active, Disabled). A "+ Create Standing Instruction" button opens the creation form containing Name (required), From and To account fields, Transfer Type, Priority, Instruction Type (Fixed, Dues), Amount, Validity From and Till dates, Recurrence Type (Periodic, As Per Dues), Recurrence Frequency, and Recurrence Interval. Standing instructions can be enabled, disabled, or deleted from the listing.

---


</description>

<workflows>
WF-001 | One-time account transfer — Submit valid transfer | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Submit | on_success: processes the transfer: debits the source account and credits the destination account
WF-002 | Enable standing instruction (row action) | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Enable | on_success: enables the standing instruction (status becomes Active) in the listing
WF-003 | Disable standing instruction (row action) | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Disable | on_success: disables the standing instruction (status becomes Disabled) in the listing
WF-004 | Delete standing instruction (row action) | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Delete | on_success: removes the standing instruction from the listing
WF-005 | Delete selected standing instructions (bulk action) | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Delete Selected | on_success: deletes the selected standing instructions from the listing
WF-006 | Open Create Standing Instruction form (toolbar action) | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: + Create Standing Instruction | on_success: opens the Standing Instruction Create form
WF-007 | Create standing instruction — Submit | actor: Authenticated user | branch: none | terminal: Create | on_success: adds the standing instruction to the listing
</workflows>

